						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Sakalalōkachakravartin Rājanārāyaṇa, Tirumallinātha Śambuvarāya: Year 16: C. 14th century.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is built in at the end.</p>						

						<p>It appears to record a gift of land in Tirubuvaṉamādēvi viḷāgam for worship and a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp to the god Tōvala Kūttappiḷḷaiyār, probably of the temple Tiruviṟkōlamuḍaiyār, in Kūvam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tiyāgasamudranallūr. The donor's name and other details are lost. Mentions a locality called Tiruveṉkāṭṭuttaḻuval.</p>						

						</summary>
